  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: _Bug_\r\n\r\n*Summary*: This is a UX issue that appears when a user is a bit sloppy. \r\nIf a user misses the usual flow and taps one extra time on 'Amount' field, he will face a UX problem with inserting amount for his transaction. User will need to tap outside the 'Amount' area and move a cursor to set it in the right spot to input the data. \r\nSimilar behaviour reproduces for both /send and /request user scenarios\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nCursor should not disappear, user should not be blocked from inserting amount at any point\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nCursor disappears when you tap on 'Amount' field, and appears again only after clicking on different areas of the input field\r\nhttps://drive.google.com/file/d/1oGl8OwSPW_yP1Ev3uMdTXaS6kA4gKWz3/view?usp=sharing\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Go to 1-1 chat\r\n- Tap on '/' icon\r\n- Tap on '/send Send a payment \r\n- Tap on 'ETH Ether'\r\n- After cursor appeared, tap on 'Amount' area\r\nNote: Similar behaviour reproduces for /request user scenario\r\n \r\n### Additional Information\r\n**Status version**: 0.9.25 (6360) node bccee2a\r\n\r\nOperating System: Genymotion emulator Samsung Galaxy S6/Android 7.1.0\r\nReal device:\r\nLenovo TAB-8703X/Android 6.0.1\r\n\r\n\r\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/HVDvOvq9ZyRjnC6Q7iNvNSEUkpt2LshvJuoU4P0T_TcaCOLc9Voqy2Wls2A=w1200-h630-p\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div>Google Drive</div><div><strong><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1oGl8OwSPW_yP1Ev3uMdTXaS6kA4gKWz3/view?usp=sharing&usp=embed_facebook\">ice_video_20180818-002253.webm</a></strong></div></blockquote>",
